The paper discusses algorithms and properties of geometric graphs, specifically the $\beta$-skeleton, in multidimensional spaces with $L_1$ and $L_{\infty}$ metrics. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also involves analyzing the structure of graphs and their properties, which can be categorized under discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GR). Finally, the paper presents algorithms for computing the $\beta$-skeleton, which can be classified under algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
